    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I have another small bikeshed to resolve: what indentation style do we prefer for doc-strings with enumerated items? Do we prefer</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"sd\">/-- Some doc-string</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">1. An item which spans multiple lines.</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">   Start of the second line.</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">2. Second item.</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">-/</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Nat</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>(i.e., three spaces),</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"sd\">/-- Some doc-string</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">1. An item which spans multiple lines.</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">  Start of the second line.</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">2. Second item.</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">-/</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Nat</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>(i.e., two spaces) or</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"sd\">/-- Some doc-string</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">1. An item which spans multiple lines.</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">    Start of the second line.</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">2. Second item.</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">-/</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Nat</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>(four spaces)?</p>",
        "id": 533102974,
        "sender_full_name": "Michael Rothgang",
        "timestamp": 1754486876
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>At the moment, mathlib uses a mix of all three styles. I'd like to unify on one of them.</p>",
        "id": 533103141,
        "sender_full_name": "Michael Rothgang",
        "timestamp": 1754486929
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Some arguments I can think of:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>two spaces is consistent with unnumbered items</li>\n<li>three and four spaces produce some alignment (which breaks once you have at least ten items --- that is rare, though)</li>\n<li>three and four spaces means linters get more complicated: enforcing two spaces is easiest to implement</li>\n</ul>",
        "id": 533103315,
        "sender_full_name": "Michael Rothgang",
        "timestamp": 1754486979
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/28041\">#28041</a> fixes more indentation (in line of the initial question of this thread)</p>",
        "id": 533104258,
        "sender_full_name": "Michael Rothgang",
        "timestamp": 1754487223
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>How about</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"mf\">1.</span><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">X</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">Y</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>(or does doc-gen support</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"bp\">#</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">X</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">Y</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>? I guess that's a header instead)</p>",
        "id": 533104344,
        "sender_full_name": "Ruben Van de Velde",
        "timestamp": 1754487244
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So, you're proposing \"five spaces\"?</p>",
        "id": 533104507,
        "sender_full_name": "Michael Rothgang",
        "timestamp": 1754487279
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I also think <code># X</code> is a header.</p>",
        "id": 533104543,
        "sender_full_name": "Michael Rothgang",
        "timestamp": 1754487293
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/28043\">#28043</a> is another small batch (+- 50 lines)</p>",
        "id": 533105705,
