    {
        "content": "<p>I also rebased/reorganized the changes in the large reformatting PR such that the commit history is hopefully more helpful when reviewing. :)</p>",
        "id": 533540902,
        "sender_full_name": "Thomas Murrills",
        "timestamp": 1754696831
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I decided to run Mathlib's docstring though <a href=\"https://mdformat.readthedocs.io/en/stable/\"><code>mdformat</code></a>, just to see what came out of it. The result, after trimming some unwanted changes, is here: <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/35686\">#35686</a></p>\n<p>Looking at the diff I see a lot of neat finds. Some changes are more opinionated, though, like always having an empty line before lists and code blocks. If nothing else, this can probably serve as inspiration for any documentation linter/formater that might be in the works.</p>",
        "id": 575367054,
        "sender_full_name": "Harald Husum",
        "timestamp": 1771871222
    },
    {
